claude
______

# Disco Limerick

There once was a dancer named Flo,
Who'd shimmer and sparkle and glow.
With platform heels high,
She'd reach for the sky,
As the mirror ball spun down below.

A DJ with records galore,
Kept the crowd moving 'round on the floor.
His beats were so funky,
The crowd got quite spunky,
And begged him to play more and more.

The disco craze swept through the land,
With polyester suits oh so grand.
The Hustle and groove,
Made everyone move,
Till the music stopped and they all sadly stand.

